		<title>Exclusive: U.S. plans new wave of immigrant deportation raids</title>


		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - U.S. immigration officials are planning a month-long series of raids in May and June to deport hundreds of Central American mothers and children found to have entered the country illegally, according to sources and an internal document seen by Reuters.<div class="feedflare">

<item>
		<title>Obama administration to issue transgender restroom guidance to schools</title>


		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - The Obama administration will tell every U.S. public school district on Friday to allow transgender students to use the bathrooms that match their gender identity.<div class="feedflare">
<a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?a=uOObAi3hcBA:mmGL3uu63K4:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?a=uOObAi3hcBA:mmGL3uu63K4:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?i=uOObAi3hcBA:mmGL3uu63K4:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?a=uOObAi3hcBA:mmGL3uu63K4:F7zBnMyn0Lo"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?i=uOObAi3hcBA:mmGL3uu63K4:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"></img></a>

<item>
		<title>U.S. Navy fires commander of sailors who were held by Iran</title>


		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - The U.S. Navy said on Thursday that it had fired the commander of the 10 American sailors who wandered into Iranian territorial waters in the Gulf in January and were briefly held by Iran in an incident that risked becoming an international crisis.<div class="feedflare">

<item>
		<title>Maryland's Joint Base Andrews locked down after bomb threat</title>


		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - Joint Base Andrews in Maryland, the military facility in suburban Washington where the presidential aircraft Air Force One is based, was put on lockdown on Thursday after a woman claiming to have a bomb strapped to her chest arrived at the visitor's center.<div class="feedflare">

<item>
		<title>World's oldest person dies in New York City, aged 116</title>


		<description>(Reuters) - The world's oldest living person, 116-year-old Susannah Mushatt Jones, died on Thursday in New York City, a research group said.<div class="feedflare">

<item>
		<title>Zimmerman offers gun used to kill Martin on new auction site: report</title>


		<description>(Reuters) - The Florida man who shot and killed black teenager Trayvon Martin, triggering nationwide civil rights protests, put his gun on a second auction website on Thursday after it was dropped by a firearm auction site that said it wanted no part in the sale.<div class="feedflare">
<a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?a=qyZPIAx925c:FwP3LUnJU3A:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?a=qyZPIAx925c:FwP3LUnJU3A:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?i=qyZPIAx925c:FwP3LUnJU3A:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?a=qyZPIAx925c:FwP3LUnJU3A:F7zBnMyn0Lo"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?i=qyZPIAx925c:FwP3LUnJU3A:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"></img></a>

<item>
		<title>U.S. courts delay execution of killer of Alabama policeman</title>


		<description>ATLANTA (Reuters) - A U.S. appeals court put on hold Thursday's scheduled execution of a 65-year-old man convicted of murdering a police officer in 1985, ordering a review of his mental competency after his lawyers said he suffers from dementia.<div class="feedflare">
<a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?a=kz6UbJN_Rvw:3xwrb_TEe58:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?a=kz6UbJN_Rvw:3xwrb_TEe58:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?i=kz6UbJN_Rvw:3xwrb_TEe58:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?a=kz6UbJN_Rvw:3xwrb_TEe58:F7zBnMyn0Lo"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/domesticNews?i=kz6UbJN_Rvw:3xwrb_TEe58:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"></img></a>

<item>
		<title>Troopers in 'disturbing' New Hampshire motorist beating suspended</title>


		<description>BOSTON (Reuters) - A state trooper from Massachusetts and another from New Hampshire were relieved of duty on Thursday for their involvement in the beating of a motorist that their commanders called "disturbing," officials said.<div class="feedflare">

<item>
		<title>New Alabama law could shutter two abortion clinics near schools</title>


		<description>(Reuters) - Alabama Governor Robert Bentley signed new abortion restrictions into law on Thursday, limiting the proximity of clinics to public schools and banning a procedure used to terminate pregnancies in the second trimester, local media reported.<div class="feedflare">

<item>
		<title>Baltimore cop failed to follow protocol: Freddie Gray prosecutor</title>


		<description>BALTIMORE (Reuters) - A white Baltimore police officer failed to follow procedures in the arrest that led to the death of Freddie Gray from a broken neck, a prosecutor said on Thursday at the start of the officer's trial.<div class="feedflare">
